      • assertAuth

        protected static void assertAuth(MessageContext theContext)
                          throws ClientException
        Assert that there are valid looking auth credentials on the context. This does not actually validate the credentials, it merely makes sure they are there. Since we know all db operations require valid credentials, if they're not present on the context, we don't have to bother making the round trip to the server to be told they're missing. We can catch that issue early and save the round trip.
        Parameters:
        theContext - the connection context to validate
        Throws:
        ClientException - if there are no auth credentials
